    "trigger_card_number": 21,
    "title": "LESSON 2: HOW TO READ A WORD",
    "header_color": "magenta",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "   When you meet an unfamiliar word, look",
          "   for three things:",
          "",
          "   1. THE PREFIX — at the front.",
          "      It tells you the direction.",
          "      ex- = out.  in- = into.",
          "",
          "   2. THE ROOT — in the middle.",
          "      It tells you the meaning.",
          "      port = carry.  dict = say.",
          "",
          "   3. THE SUFFIX — at the end.",
          "      It tells you the word type.",
          "      -ion = noun.  -ive = adjective.",
          "",
          "   ex + port = carry out. That's it."
        ],
